commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Hardik Pandya will open the attack

Hardik Pandya to Saha, FOUR, Saha gets going with a boundary! The crowd goes berserk. Bit of shape away from the right-hander but there's too much width outside off. Saha cuts through point and the ball speeds away to the fence
Hardik Pandya to Saha, 1 run, 136.3kph, good length and just outside off, Saha opens the bat-face to guide it to third man
Pandya has dismissed Shubman Gill thrice in 5 balls in IPL. This should be a mouth-watering duel

Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, no run, 132.3kph, full on leg and Shubman Gill is livid with himself as he clips it straight to midwicket. A couple of inches either side and that would have been a boundary

Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 138.8kph, Gill doesn't miss out on this occasion! Full ball swinging into the pads and Gill flicks it away to get off the mark with a boundary. No chance for long leg to even get close to it

Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, no run, 135.4kph, appeal for caught behind from Ishan Kishan, Rohit didn't hear anything at first slip and even the bowler isn't confident. Shubman Gill skips down the track to drive this fullish delivery over the off-side and is beaten on the outside edge as the ball straightens a bit off the deck. UltraEdge confirms no edge!
Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 134.1kph, short of length ball, chopped to cover who fumbles and that results in a brace
Luke Wood from the other end. Watch out for his inswingers. No slip...
Luke Wood, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Wood to Saha, no run, short of length ball that curls in towards off, a hopping Saha taps it into the off-side
Wood to Saha, 1 run, hits the deck hard and gets good bounce from a back of a length, a hopping Saha dabs it towards short third man
Deep backward square leg moves slightly to his right
Wood to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 139.8kph, fuller than a good length, Gill looks to clip, uppish but safe. Well wide of midwicket and goes to mid-on on the bounce
Wood to Saha, no run, 142.4kph, very full and that's been jammed to the right of the bowler
Wood to Saha, leg byes, 1 run, 138.8kph, pad-lined and Wood gets away, Saha looks to swing it away but misses and the ball rolls towards square leg off his thigh
Wood to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 140.1kph, Wood pulls his length back and that sits up nicely for the batter. Gill stands tall and punches it through mid-off. Excellent timing. Mid-off was too wide
Hardik Pandya to Saha, FOUR, 127.2kph, full and wide of off, Saha gets forward and opens the bat-face to drive it to the right of the diving backward point fielder. The quick outfield does the rest

Hardik Pandya to Saha, FOUR, 120.2kph, pace off but it's a floaty half-volley outside off. Saha presses forward and drives through extra cover off the bottom part of the bat. A teasing chase for Coetzee who runs back and slides but the ball wins the race
Hardik Pandya to Saha, 1 run, 136.3kph, very full, driven towards mid-on for a quick single
Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, no run, 128.8kph, length ball marginally outside off and Gill defends it towards cover
Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, no run, 140kph, shapes away a bit from a length, Gill looks to work it into the leg-side and gets a leading edge towards short third man
Hardik Pandya to Shubman Gill, no run, 134.5kph, stays leg-side of the ball and pats this short of a good length ball to cover
We have a bowling change and here's MI's spearhead...
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah to Saha, no run, 134.9kph, in-slanting short of length ball, Saha hops and defends with a closed bat-face
Bumrah to Saha, no run, 119.1kph, off-cutter, not picked by the batter. Saha checks his drive and the ball hits him high on the bat before dying down on the leg-side
Bumrah to Saha, no run, 141kph, short of length, no room on offer, Saha looks to tap and run. But the bowler is quick to get to the ball
Bumrah to Saha, FOUR, 119.8kph, pace off, Saha's bottom hand comes off the bat handle as he goes for the aerial drive. But he's made decent contact to elevate it over mid-off
Bumrah to Saha, no run, 139.8kph, full and darted in, Saha flicks and gets an inside edge onto his pad
Bumrah to Saha, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Bumrah to Saha, out Bowled!! Trademark Bumrah! 140.6kph yorker angled in from wide of the crease. Right in the blockhole, Saha is not only late to bring his bat down but also ends up playing outside the line. The ball crashes into the base of the middle-stump. Bumrah strikes in his opening over, has his arms aloft with a beaming smile on his face. Saha b Bumrah 19(15) [4s-4]
Spin time. A slip in place
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Shams Mulani, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 100.3kph, non-turner from round the wicket, Shubman Gill works it into the midwicket pocket for a single
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 84.6kph, clipped towards backward square leg for a single
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, no run, 83.5kph, nudged into the leg-side
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, FOUR, 81.7kph, slow, short and wide. Gill waits on the back foot and fiercely cuts through the covers. Poor ball and Gill pounces
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, no run, 85.8kph, in-drifter, Gill misses the clip to get hit on the front leg. Half an appeal for lbw but that's sliding down leg

Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, SIX, 83.kph, drifting in on leg and Shubman Gill gets down on one leg to slogsweep it over deep backward square leg. High and handsome. Used the bowler's angle to his advantage. First six of the match and Shams concedes 12 runs off his first over in IPL
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 91.6kph, googly outside off, low bounce as well, Sudharsan pulls to deep midwicket
Chawla to Shubman Gill, no run, 86.1kph, probably another googly, off-stump line, Gill defends from the crease
Chawla to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 87.6kph, pushed through quicker and the line is straighter, worked through midwicket
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 92.9kph, wrong 'un that keeps low outside off, Sudharsan hammers the pull to midwicket and there's a slight mix-up. Gill gets sent back and the throw isn't on target
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 94.8kph, quicker one, punched to extra cover

Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, 87.8kph, punched between extra cover and mid-off. Beats Rohit to his left and then a diving Hardik can only half-stop it. Runs back and stops it to keep the batters down to two

Powerplay highlights -- Hardik opens the bowling for MI -- Both GT openers score a boundary in the 1st over -- Saha hits Hardik for 2 successive boundaries in his 2nd over -- Bumrah cleans up Saha with a terrific yorker -- Gill hammers Mulani for a four and a six off his 1st over -- 3 dots, 4 runs off Piyush Chawla's opening over
Timeout!
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, 1 run, round the wicket, bit of spin from a short of length, Shubman Gill punches it to long-off
Over the wicket to Sai Sudharsan
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 90.6kph, fuller and quicker on middle, Sai Sudharsan clips it to midwicket
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 80.9kph, Mulani pulls his length back by a fraction and Sai Sudharsan rocks back to punch it to long-off
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 92.1kph, sliding down leg, Gill is late on the flick and inside-edges it fine of Chawla at short fine leg
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, wide, 90kph, spills this length ball well down leg
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 80.7kph, decent bounce from a length, Gill waits and cuts to deep backward point
Shubman Gill moves away very late but Mulani delivers the ball. It's a dead ball
Shams Mulani to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, 79.2kph, slider on off, scythed to deep backward point for another brace
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 5 wides, 84.6kph, on seeing the line down leg, Sudharsan shapes to sweep hard. He misses, so does the keeper and the ball runs away to the fence
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 90.4kph, off-stump line, Sudharsan cuts to deep point off the back foot
Chawla to Shubman Gill, 1 run, 85.6kph, tossed up, full around off and Gill drives it to sweeper cover
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 83.2kph, flighted ball, Sai Sudharsan skips down the track and wristily drives it to long-on
Chawla to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chawla to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Rohit!! Chawla gets the big fish. 86kph, googly, not much spin, Shubman Gill dances down the track to loft it. Doesn't get the necessary elevation and holes out to long-on. Rohit takes a few steps to his left and takes a safe catch. Shubman Gill c Rohit b Chawla 31(22) [4s-3 6s-1]
A slip in place now
Azmatullah Omarzai, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chawla to Azmatullah, 1 run, Omarzai gets forward and drives along the ground to long-off
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 91.8kph, flicked to deep midwicket off the back foot
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 93kph, quick in-turner, clipped to the left of midwicket where Hardik makes a sharp stop
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 90.9kph, leg-lined, tucked to deep square leg
Shams Mulani to Azmatullah, no run, 83.9kph, off-stump line, Omarzai backs away and cuts straight to Bumrah at wide backward point
Shams Mulani to Azmatullah, 1 run, 94.2kph, driven to long-off
Shams Mulani to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 90.9kph, very full outside off, Sudharsan squeeze-drives to sweeper cover
Shams Mulani to Azmatullah, no run, 82.5kph, hint of spin from a length and that's been punched straight to cover
Naman Dhir, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Naman Dhir to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, 85.7kph, Sai Sudharsan greets Naman Dhir with a boundary. Shortish offie outside off and the left-hander pounces. Rocks back in his crease and slaps it over the covers in the direction of the spin
Naman Dhir to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 83.9kph, slider on off, Sudharsan punches wide of cover
Over the wicket now

Naman Dhir to Azmatullah, FOUR, Azmatullah gets low and heaves it away over square leg. Two fielders (Tilak and Coetzee) converge, the ball lands in front of them and spins away from Coetzee to go to the fence. That won't please the bowler
Naman Dhir to Azmatullah, 1 run, 94.9kph, knocked through wide mid-on
Naman Dhir to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, stays back and tucks through square leg for a brace
Naman Dhir to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 89.5kph, nudged into the on-side and Sudharsan will keep the strike. 13 runs off the over
Piyush Chawla [2.0-0-14-1] is back into the attack
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, shot! 87.1kph, flighted ball but it's just outside leg, Sai Sudharsan gets down on one leg and sweeps fiercely over deep backward square leg. Hit hard and superbly
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, Sai Sudharsan whips this full delivery through midwicket

Chawla to Azmatullah, 1 run, 86.5kph, Azmatullah comes down the track premeditatively and yorks himself in the process. Brings his bat down just in time to ekes out an inside edge towards short fine leg
Chawla to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, punched to long-off
Chawla to Azmatullah, SIX, just over long-on! 85.1kph, tossed up ball, full in length and Azmatullah bends his back leg to club it downtown. Even Tim David can't get there with a jump...
Chawla to Azmatullah, 2 runs, 85.3kph, worked in front of square on the leg-side and Azmatullah comes back for the second. 17 runs off the over!
30 runs off the last two overs and here's Coetzee on IPL debut
Gerald Coetzee, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 137.2kph, hard length, off-stump line, Sudharsan pokes it to backward point
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 142.3kph, hits the deck hard on a shortish length and Sudharsan hurriedly pulls through midwicket
Gerald Coetzee to Azmatullah, 1 run, 145.3kph, in-slanter on the stumps from a good length, Azmatullah stays leg-side and taps it to backward point. A misfield from Rohit results in a single
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, 144.5kph, fuller than a length, push-driven to the left of deep cover
Fine leg and deep square leg in place. Short ball?

Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, leg byes, 1 run, 147kph skiddy length ball, Sudharsan is late on the flick and loses his balance as he gets hit on the pad. Optimistic appeal for lbw from Coetzee but that pitched well outside leg
Gerald Coetzee to Azmatullah, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Azmatullah, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Maiden IPL wicket for Gerald Coetzee! And he's pumped up. 145.8kph, cross-seam delivery, it's the hard length and Azmatullah looks to swing it over midwicket. Doesn't quite middle it, ore height than distance. Tilak, at deep square leg, settles under it and gathers it. Azmatullah c Tilak Varma b Gerald Coetzee 17(11) [4s-1 6s-1]
David Miller, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Jasprit Bumrah [1.0-0-4-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, punched through extra cover
Bumrah to Miller, no run, round the wicket, length ball, Miller defends
Bumrah to Miller, 1 run, 121.2kph, off-pace ball, Miller jams it down the pitch. Hardik moves to his left from mid-off and acrobatically half-stops. Boos from the Ahmedabad crowd
Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 137.9kph, short ball, Sudharsan sways away from it

Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 140.6kph, low full toss, meant to be the yorker, Sudharsan brings his bat down hurriedly to flick and is saved by an inside edge. Half an appeal for lbw but MI rightly don't review it
Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, no run, bumper to end the over, Sudharsan tries to ramp it over the keeper but fails to make contact

Gerald Coetzee to Miller, leg byes, 1 run, oh trouble, trouble and Miller escapes! Sai Sudharsan wanted a brisk run and ended up almost selling his partner down the river. Miller was no way getting home in time having paused initially. This was a pact short of length delivery that thudded the pad from round the wicket, Miller missed the glance, ball went to cover-point. Fielder took quick aim and released but was off target
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of length dn angling in, Sai works it through backward square leg
Gerald Coetzee to Miller, 1 run, late dab past backward point as Miller lets this short of length delivery come to him

Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, over the wicket and rushing Sai with a short of length delivery but Sai shows his class by rocking back and muscling the pull shot between deep mid-wicket and deep backward square

Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, no run, oh he wanted the upper cut but missed! Short and angling away, Sai looks to cut hard, ball flies close to the edge and they put out a soft appeal for caught behind
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 145.3kph attempted yorker that goes as low full toss, wristed to deep mid-wicket

Timeout! 6 overs to go. This is fun time for a batter in the first innings in Ahmedabad usually but there is Bumrah today. Need a minimum of 180 on this pitch. Ah we already see droplets on the outfield! Dew is in attendance today
Hardik Pandya [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, slower delivery from round the wicket, Sai clips it to mid-on
We have an intruder! It's a dog that's stealing the show running on the outfield
Hardik Pandya to Miller, 1 run, we are back for a back of a length from the same angle, Miller pulls to deep mid-wicket

Hardik Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, sliced away and how smart! Proper cricketing shot under pressure with team needing 10 per over at least. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Sai opens the bat face late, beats point and third man is a ball-watcher. No chance for him
The dog wants a share of the fun again. Pause in play
Hardik Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, slower ball bouncer but Sai plays a controlled pull behind square past short fine leg, protection in the deep though
Hardik Pandya to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, driven along the ground to long-on
Hardik Pandya to Miller, 1 run, shortish delivery, Miller pulls through deep square leg
10 off that over with minimal risk
Gerald Coetzee to Miller, 2 runs, oh would have been an off-side wide but Miller spots vacant spots behind cover and reaches out to tap this slower delivery in the gap

Middle overs (7-15) highlights -- Piyush Chawla gets the big fish (Gill) in the 8th over -- After 2 successive non-boundary overs, Gill looks to loft Chawla and holes out -- Mulani redeems himself with a couple of tight overs -- Naman Dhir goes for 13 in his opening over -- Piyush Chawla 1st 2 overs - 14 runs, his 3rd over - 17. -- Coetzee picks up Omarzai in his maiden IPL over -- Miller escapes a narrow run-out on 1
Gerald Coetzee to Miller, FOUR, crashed through cover! Full delivery outside off stump, Miller leans into the drive and creams it past cover this time with power
Gerald Coetzee to Miller, 1 run, full and wide of off stump, Miller guides it point.
Looks like they are going to bowl only wide yorkers to Miller
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Sai glances it through backward square leg
Gerald Coetzee to Miller, 1 run, oh he got away with a leg-side gift! Fine leg in so Miller thought of the tickle but glanced it straight to hand
Gerald Coetzee to Sai Sudharsan, no run, oh tried to be too cheeky and went for the scoop, played it onto his pad and it's a dot
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-6-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Miller, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Miller, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! In the airrrr, mighty high and really well taken by Hardik. Look at him celebrate with extra joy. Is it about Miller the dangerous man out or is out about the boos? But what a lovely slower delivery this is from Boom. Sucked Miller way too early into the drive, the tease was there with mid-off up and Miller played one handed as he got completely deceived. Hardik moved back to complete a what looked simple but tough catch. Miller c Hardik Pandya b Bumrah 12(11) [4s-1]
Vijay Shankar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Shankar, 1 run, played off the outer half of the bat and goes past point
Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! In the airrrr and that's a really good low catch. Juggled a bit but he clutched it onto his body. Tough catch with the background. This was a bonus wicket for Bumrah. Short of a length delivery angling in, Sai flicks, 4 metres either side would have been a boundary but kudos to Tilak for judging it to perfection by running in and timing the forward dive spot on. Bumrah has broke open the game in this over. Sai Sudharsan c Tilak Varma b Bumrah 45(39) [4s-3 6s-1]
Rahul Tewatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, no run, oh almost deceived him with a slower delivery, Tewatia early into the push back to the bowler
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Tewatia guides to backward point
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, goes for the killer yorker, Tewatia flicks it to mid-wicket
180 seems tough now, but Tewatia is tough too. Somehow they need to find a way to 180. One each for Bumrah and Coetzee. Luke Wood comes on now
Luke Wood [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack

Wood to Rahul Tewatia, SIX, there he goes, down the ground over long-off. The leg-cutting back of the hand slower delivery, but Tewatia spotted that from a distance like a hawk, waited for the down swing of the bat and smacked it over the rope
Wood to Rahul Tewatia, no run, short of length delivery angling in, Tewatia beaten the pull, ball brushed the thigh pad and goes on the bounce to keeper

Wood to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, smart, really smart from Tewatia! He's injected life again straightaway. Pacy short of length delivery outside off stump, third man up, yeah I can have a slice now says Tewatia and he opens the bat face late to steal a boundary

Wood to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, and again! This time with more swag! This will irk the bowling coach because he has third man up and he offered short with a loft of width outside off stump. Tewatia stays back and guides it over the infield for four more

Wood to Rahul Tewatia, 2 runs, they got mid-off up for this ball and Tewatia goes aerial over that region. Took a really good slide at the ropes from Hardik to save two. Full delivery, Tewatia took toll with a drive
Wood to Rahul Tewatia, no ball, oh dear, high beamer, clear no ball and Tewatia sways out of the line to avoid injury. Wood apologizes. That seemed to have slipped. 150 up and there's a free-hit too

Wood to Rahul Tewatia, wide, he tried the short delivery, Tewatia tried to guide it over the keeper but it's too high and the free-hit stays. Wonder why Hardik chose Wood over Coetzee for this over. It could have been Coetzee, Bumrah and then Wood if he needed
Wood to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, short delivery, Tewatia pulls to deep square leg and wants more fun, so keeps strike
Tewatia has done a great job. Can he take down Bumrah too?
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, leg byes, 1 run, appeal for LBW as Bumrah goes full from over the wicket, Tewatia swung and got hit on the pad, pitched outside leg
Bumrah to Shankar, 1 run, advances and yorks himself up, 141kph, Shankar manages to dig out

Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, 2 runs, shuffles in the crease to put the bowler off, it's a low full toss from Bumrah, Tewatia flicks along the ground. Brilliant sliding save to the right of deep mid-wicket to save two
How far is the slower ball away?
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, not far, because Bumrah nails the slower ball yorker, Tewatia flicks it to long-on
Bumrah to Shankar, 1 run, oh friendly full toss and even more kind of Vijay Shankar to just gently tap it to long-on than give it a whack
Bumrah to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, shuffles again, leg stump yorker almost, Tewatia drags it through mid-wicket off the inside edge
Bumrah ends with an incredible 4-0-14-3 on a good batting pitch
Naman Dhir has taken a stunner, they are checking if it is clean. Fingers under it, gone!
Gerald Coetzee [3.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Rahul Tewatia, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Rahul Tewatia, out Caught by Naman Dhir!! In the airrrrr and what a stunning catch that is by Naman Dhir. He's made a massive impact on his IPL debut. This could make a difference at of at least 10 runs. Tewatia tried to get under this low full toss and swing it away for a maximum, but it went off the bottom of the bat. Didn't look like a catch but Dhir ran in from deep backward square leg, dived full length forward and took it just inches off the grass. Need multiple angles to confirm fingers under the ball. But great hand from Tewatia ends! Rahul Tewatia c Naman Dhir b Gerald Coetzee 22(15) [4s-2 6s-1]
Rashid Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Rashid Khan, 2 runs, short of length delivery, Rashid toe-ends the slog to square leg and he steals two
Gerald Coetzee to Rashid Khan, 1 run, and again, this time to mid-wicket and only one
Gerald Coetzee to Shankar, 1 run, yorker on the off stump, Shankar digs it out to mid-wicket, thinks of two but Rashid Khan says no I will have the strike. Run wasn't on anyway
Gerald Coetzee to Rashid Khan, 1 run, swings hard but it's only a toe-ender to long-on and Rashid very disappointed he didn't connect and drags himself slowly to long-on

Gerald Coetzee to Shankar, 2 runs, low full toss, flicked to deep mid-wicket, they try to steal the second run. Rashid could be in trouble as the throw it right over the stumps and Coetzee does really well to ignite the stumps having to collect from a height and Rashid has just got home in time

21:16 Local Time, 15:46 GMT, 21:16 IST: If the Mumbai Indians needed the best conditions to erase their first game curse since 2013, they have it right in front here. The Titans have finished below par when even 180 doesn't look to be appealing because of the dew. But MI will be wary of their history and will want to do this sensibly. The new ball here in the second innings is a real tough time to bat but can the dew negate the factor? We will find out!

Jasprit Bumrah! Yes, he was the one solely responsible for the Titans finishing this low. When people were wondering why Bumrah wasn't bowled for 3 overs he came on and knocked out a good-looking Saha with his typical toe-crusher. Gill was looking well set too until he gifted Chawla a wicket trying to hit a maximum. Sai did his usual bit batting first innings in the IPL. Bumrah came back to get both Miller and Sai in the same over. It took a smart cameo from Tewatia to get this past 160, otherwise they were finishing even lower. Coetzee was impressive on his IPL debut, while Luke Wood wasn't. Back in 15 for the chase.

Sai Sudharsan: I feel the wicket is a bit tricky and even the bounce is a bit low. They were getting some turn. I think this is a good target, hopefully we save it. I felt this is not a wicket where you can just go after the bowler every ball, every over. So I was just thinking of building the middle overs nicely and giving it to the finishers. He (Bumrah) bowled really well today and executed really well, I actually enjoyed that match-up. The dew is also little less today, so I feel that the spinners might come into play and it might grip a little.
MI bowling \nBumrah and Coetzee: 5/41 from 8 overs (ER: 5.125) \nOthers: 1/123 from 12 overs (ER: 10.25)

GT bowlers in the powerplay in IPL 2023 Mohammed Shami: 17 wickets at 19.41, SR: 15.53, ER: 7.5 Others: 8 wickets at 63.87, SR: 42, ER: 9.12 No other bowler bagged more than 10 wickets in the powerplay last season.
Welcome back. If the Titans get the new ball moving around, this could be fun. Mohit the impact sub for GT for Sai!
